little time mingle with the raw vegetables. If you do this just cover and refrigerate until you are ready to serve. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eYou can substitute sugar for honey\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eOther additions you could try: more fresh herbs like dill or cilantro, or more spices like cayenne, turmeric or cumin. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eWhile I like coleslaw made a few hours ahead, I’ll also say I prefer to eat it within 24 hours of being made. While it can last longer if stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator it also tends to get mushy overtime.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1200\" data-pin-url=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/coleslaw/?tp_image_id=139682\" data-pin-title=\"coleslaw\" src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe.jpg 1200w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-300x300.jpg 300w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-150x150.jpg 150w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-768x768.jpg 768w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-100x100.jpg 100w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-60x60.jpg 60w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-750x750.jpg 750w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-730x730.jpg 730w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-700x700.jpg 700w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-550x550.jpg 550w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/coleslaw-recipe-156x156.jpg 156w, https://abeautifulmess.com